      "content": "I hear the immense hopelessness in your words, and it sounds like you are feeling utterly depleted and final. When a part of us feels as lost as you describe, it can make the idea of \"fixing\" feel insulting or futile. Perhaps instead of focusing on repair, we could explore ways to acknowledge and meet this present feeling of emptiness with kindness, rather than trying to resurrect the past. This acknowledgment itself can sometimes create a small space for new, unexpected moments of connection.",
      "source": "target",
