      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feeling like you are taking up meaningless space carries a truly enormous weight, and it is understandable that you are exhausted by the idea of effort. When everything feels heavy and pointless, the goal isn't necessarily to find a future, but simply to lighten the load of the present moment. Could we focus on identifying one tiny, manageable thing that requires the least amount of energy right now, maybe just for the next five minutes? Even the smallest pause can sometimes interrupt the crushing momentum of feeling pointless.",
      "source": "target",
